Having a common path geometry19, epi-MISS, and el-epi-MISS are characterized by low temporal path-length noise. The temporal noise of el-epi-MISS is given by the standard deviation of the DFT phase-amplitude at the electrical actuation frequency for each pixel and is ~ 0.3 ± 0.1° (Supplementary materials), yielding an SNR of ~30 dB for the electroactive area (SNR=10Log[10,(S/N)2]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
